replies.body:
I have to disagree personally. Snowballing is already a huge issue, and frankly the proposal that 'Kills should do more/give more XP' is just begging for more people with the Bronzeâ„¢ mentality that 'Kills are worth more than everything; Fuck you'. Plus the fact that the XP-rubberband is for people that are like. SEVERELY behind. i'm talking laner is somehow 5 levels ahead behind, because then you cross into the territory of having a useless teammate and that doesn't feel fun for the player, their team, and sometimes even the enemy team (There's some people that'll kill the person who was DC'ed for the first five mins, and then the actual crowd with decency).
Plus I. Don't really see a problem with the Homeguard buff. Once again, getting rid of that would further increase the power of snowballing imo.

All other points are pretty reasonable though. I almost cried when they removed Stealth Wards ;~; {{sticker:zombie-nunu-tears}}
